00:31:12.690 --> 00:31:14.666
DALE HUMBY: Hey, everyone.

00:31:14.666 --> 00:31:19.250
A few weeks ago, we had
the Google Developer Summit

00:31:19.250 --> 00:31:22.750
in Africa, and that was held
in three cities-- in Lagos

00:31:22.750 --> 00:31:25.850
on the 19th of August,
in Nairobi on the 22nd,

00:31:25.850 --> 00:31:28.500
and in Cape Town on
the 25th of August.

00:31:28.500 --> 00:31:31.220
And this was an event
hosted by Google,

00:31:31.220 --> 00:31:33.780
and a lot of the Google
developer experts

00:31:33.780 --> 00:31:35.370
from around Africa.

00:31:35.370 --> 00:31:37.850
It was a two track
conference over one day,

00:31:37.850 --> 00:31:44.030
and the first track was focused
on material design for Android,

00:31:44.030 --> 00:31:49.410
and the second track
was cloud and web track.

00:31:49.410 --> 00:31:53.270
And, you know, for me, I
attended the cloud and web

00:31:53.270 --> 00:31:56.210
track, being a cloud
GDE, and I think

00:31:56.210 --> 00:31:59.030
one of the-- what was made
really exciting for me was

00:31:59.030 --> 00:32:02.030
that most people in Africa,
they access their internet

00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:04.630
through the phones, or
through their cell phones,

00:32:04.630 --> 00:32:10.860
and it's a barrier to entry,
having to download and install

00:32:10.860 --> 00:32:12.840
applications if you're
an app developer,

00:32:12.840 --> 00:32:19.430
and so having really great
mobile web apps on your phone

00:32:19.430 --> 00:32:22.450
is-- well, being able to attract
an audience on that is good,

00:32:22.450 --> 00:32:24.690
because it means you
don't have to worry

00:32:24.690 --> 00:32:26.760
about doing the installation.

00:32:26.760 --> 00:32:29.600
And these two talks
focused on new tools

00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:34.710
for web developers, which bring
web app functionality closer

00:32:34.710 --> 00:32:37.370
to that of mobile applications.

00:32:37.370 --> 00:32:40.820
The first talk was on push
notifications for Chrome,

00:32:40.820 --> 00:32:45.920
and this allows web apps to send
notifications-- or a website

00:32:45.920 --> 00:32:50.120
to send notifications-- down
to the website on your Chrome

00:32:50.120 --> 00:32:55.600
browser, just as, as it were,
like on the Android devices,

00:32:55.600 --> 00:33:00.610
like native Android
push notifications.

00:33:00.610 --> 00:33:04.020
The second talk was on
offline page caching,

00:33:04.020 --> 00:33:07.930
which is one of my favorite
technologies at the moment.

00:33:07.930 --> 00:33:10.640
This allows your web
app to cache data

00:33:10.640 --> 00:33:14.250
so it can still work even
when the app's offline,

00:33:14.250 --> 00:33:19.230
and then synchronize when
you get your connection back,

00:33:19.230 --> 00:33:21.770
and that could be because
you choose to switch off

00:33:21.770 --> 00:33:23.440
your data because
you're roaming,

00:33:23.440 --> 00:33:27.220
or it could be because you're
just on a poor data connection.

00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:30.930
So those are the two talks
that I attended while there,

00:33:30.930 --> 00:33:35.230
and if you would like a
summit-- a Google summit--

00:33:35.230 --> 00:33:38.630
